Case Based, Abductive Reasoning. 

Case-based reasoning is explicitly mentioned in the paper as a component of the ADAPtER system, which uses a case memory and adaptation mechanisms to solve new cases based on past experience. Abductive reasoning is also a key component, as the system uses a logical model and abductive reasoning with consistency constraints to solve complex diagnostic problems involving multiple faults. The paper does not mention any other sub-categories of AI.
